HOUSE BILL 571
C9, Q1 6lr1818
CF SB 369
By: Delegate Allen
Introduced and read first time: January 28, 2026
Assigned to: Economic Matters
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 10, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Nonprofit Housing Corporations – Tax and Enforcement of Judgment Taxes and
3 Special Assessments Exemptions – Alterations
4 FOR the purpose of altering the definition of “nonprofit housing corporation” for purposes
5 of eligibility for an exemption from real property taxes and special assessments of
6 the State or a political subdivision; exempting certain real property owned by certain
7 subsidiary entities of a nonprofit housing corporation from taxes and special
8 assessments of the State or a political subdivision; exempting certain real property
9 of a nonprofit housing corporation from certain procedures for enforcement of a
10 judgment against the nonprofit housing corporation; and generally relating to tax
11 and enforcement of judgment taxes and special assessments exemptions for
12 nonprofit housing corporations.
13 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
14 Article – Housing and Community Development
15 Section 12–104
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2019 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
20 Article – Housing and Community Development
21 12–104.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0571*

2 HOUSE BILL 571
1 (a) In this section, “housing authority entity” means an entity:
2 (1) that is controlled or wholly owned by an authority; or
3 (2) in which an authority or an entity controlled or wholly owned by an
4 authority has an ownership interest, either directly or indirectly, through one or more
5 wholly or partially owned subsidiary entities.
6 (b) A nonprofit entity shall be deemed controlled by an authority under subsection
7 (a) of this section if:
8 (1) the nonprofit entity is established by an authority under § 12–502(h) of
9 this title; and
10 (2) the authority:
11 (i) has the power to appoint a majority of the board of directors of
12 the nonprofit entity; or
13 (ii) is the sole member of the nonprofit entity.
14 (c) (1) (I) In this subsection, THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE
15 MEANINGS INDICATED.
16 (II) “AFFORDABLE HOUSING” MEANS RENTAL HOUSING:
17 1. THAT HAS BEEN AWARDED OR APPROVED FOR A
18 CREDIT ALLOWED UNDER § 42 OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND IS SUBJECT
19 TO A COVENANT UNDER THE FEDERAL LOW–INCOME HOUSING TAX CREDIT
20 PROGRAM; OR
21 2. APPROVED BY THE GOVERNING BODY OF THE
22 POLITICAL SUBDIVISION IN WHICH THE PROJECT IS LOCATED AND FOR WHICH:
23 A. AT LEAST 50% OF THE UNITS ARE RESERVED FOR
24 HOUSEHOLDS EARNING AT OR BELOW 60% OF THE AREA MEDIAN INCOME FOR THE
25 METROPOLITAN STATISTICAL AREA OF THE PROJECT; AND
26 B. RENT IS RESTRICTED TO 30% OF GROSS HOUSEHOLD
27 INCOME FOR A FAMILY OF FOUR AT OR BELOW 60% OF THE AREA MEDIAN INCOME
28 FOR THE METROPOLITAN STATISTICAL AREA OF THE PROJECT, ADJUSTED TO 1.5
29 INDIVIDUALS FOR EACH BEDROOM IN THE UNIT.
30 (III) “nonprofit NONPROFIT housing corporation” means a [nonprofit
31 or charitable private corporation that provides safe and sanitary housing to persons of

HOUSE BILL 571 3
1 eligible income in such a way that the corporation works essentially like an authority under
2 this Division II] CORPORATION:
3 (I) 1. INCORPORATED UNDER THE LAWS OF THE STATE OR
4 AUTHORIZED TO DO BUSINESS IN THE STATE BY THE STATE DEPARTMENT OF
5 ASSESSMENTS AND TAXATION;
6 (II) 2. RECOGNIZED BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE
7 AS AN ORGANIZATION DESCRIBED IN § 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE;
8 AND
9 (III) 3. ORGANIZED AND OPERATED FOR THE PRIMARY
10 PURPOSE OF DEVELOPING, OWNING, OR OPERATING SAFE AND SANITARY
11 AFFORDABLE HOUSING FOR PERSONS OF ELIGIBLE INCOME.
12 (2) THIS SUBSECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO A HOUSING PROJECT
13 OWNED BY A NONPROFIT HOUSING CORPORATION OR AN ENTITY THAT IS
14 CONTROLLED OR WHOLLY OWNED BY A NONPROFIT HOUSING CORPORATION THAT,
15 BEFORE JULY 1, 2026, RECEIVED A FINANCIAL CONTRIBUTION, INCLUDING A LOAN,
16 A GRANT, OR OTHER DIRECT FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF
17 THE HOUSING PROJECT FROM A POLITICAL SUBDIVISION IN WHICH THE HOUSING
18 PROJECT IS LOCATED.
19 (2) (3) Property is used for essential public and governmental OR
20 CHARITABLE purposes and is exempt from all taxes and special assessments of the State
21 or a political subdivision if the property:
22 (i) belongs to an authority or a nonprofit housing corporation;
23 (ii) is used as housing for persons of eligible income and is owned in
24 whole or in part, directly or indirectly, through one or more wholly or partially owned
25 subsidiary entities of a housing authority entity OR NONPROFIT HOUSING
26 CORPORATION; or
27 (iii) 1. is used, or if planned or under construction will be used,
28 as housing for persons of eligible income and is owned in whole or in part, directly or
29 indirectly, through one or more wholly or partially owned subsidiary entities of a housing
30 authority entity OR NONPROFIT HOUSING CORPORATION; and
31 2. has improvements, or has improvements planned or under
32 construction, located on land that is owned by:
33 A. an authority OR A NONPROFIT HOUSING
34 CORPORATION; or

4 HOUSE BILL 571
1 B. an entity that is controlled or wholly owned by an
2 authority OR A NONPROFIT HOUSING CORPORATION.
3 (3) (4) In lieu of those taxes and special assessments, an authority, a
4 nonprofit housing corporation, or a housing authority entity shall pay the political
5 subdivision in which a housing project is wholly or partly located an amount, if any, that
6 may be set by mutual agreement and that does not exceed the amount of regular taxes
7 levied on similar property.
8 (d) (1) Except as provided in paragraph (2) or (3) of this subsection:
9 (i) all real property of an authority is exempt from levy and sale by
10 virtue of an execution;
11 (II) ALL REAL PROPERTY OF A NONPROFIT HOUSING
12 CORPORATION THAT IS USED AS HOUSING FOR PERSONS OF ELIGIBLE INCOME IS
13 EXEMPT FROM LEVY AND SALE BY VIRTUE OF AN EXECUTION;
14 [(ii)] (III) an execution or other judicial process may not issue
15 against the real property DESCRIBED IN ITEMS (I) AND (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH; [and]
16 [(iii)] (IV) a judgment against an authority is not a charge or lien on
17 the authority’s real property; AND
18 (V) A JUDGMENT AGAINST A NONPROFIT HOUSING
19 CORPORATION IS NOT A CHARGE OR LIEN ON THE NONPROFIT HOUSING
20 CORPORATION’S REAL PROPERTY THAT IS USED AS HOUSING FOR PERSONS OF
21 ELIGIBLE INCOME.
22 (2) Paragraph (1) of this subsection does not limit a right to foreclose or
23 otherwise enforce:
24 (i) a mortgage or deed of trust recorded against property of an
25 authority OR A NONPROFIT HOUSING CORPORATION; or
26 (ii) a pledge or lien given by an authority OR A NONPROFIT
27 HOUSING CORPORATION on its rents, fees, or revenues.
28 (3) This subsection does not deprive a political subdivision of its right to
29 collect money agreed to be paid in lieu of taxes in the same manner as taxes are now or may
30 be collected under State law and the laws of the political subdivision.
31 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
32 1, 2026.

